{
  "text": "(1) the general element A in the pencil | \u2212 K E(3) | is a smooth, abelian surface isogenous to E \u00d7 E, and the restriction of \u03b2 : E(3) \u2212\u2192 E to A gives rise to a smooth, isotrivial elliptic fibration A \u2212\u2192 E. Moreover the pencil contains four singular elliptic scrolls A 1 , . . . , A 4 ; (2) any X \u03b7i is a smooth bielliptic surface of type 6 (see Chapter VI of [CITATION_1] ). The restriction of \u03b2 gives rise to a smooth, isotrivial elliptic fibration X \u03b7i \u2212\u2192 E, whereas the pencil | \u2212 K E(3) | cuts out on X \u03b7i an isotrivial pencil of elliptic curves with three triple fibres.",
